    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 81.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[By cable.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. E. B. Washburne</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12, 1870</date>. (Received September 12,
                                1870.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Government requests me to use my good offices, unofficially, and simply
                            as a citizen, to hold intercourse with Prussian government. Have
                            declined until I can hear from you. Immediate answer important.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WASHBURNE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
